 [[Australian Touring Car Championship]] consisted of ten rounds.\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 90%\"\n|-\n!Rd.\n!Race Title\n!Circuit\n!City / State\n!Date\n!Winner\n!Team\n!Report\n|-\n! 1\n| [[Amaroo Park ATCC round|Better Brakes 100]]\n| [[Amaroo Park]]\n| [[Sydney]], [[New South Wales]]\n| 1 - 2 Mar\n| [[Robbie Francevic]]\n| [[Mark Petch Motorsport]]\n|\n|-\n! 2\n| [[Australian National Line|A.N.L.]] [[Symmons Plains ATCC round|Cup]]\n| [[Symmons Plains Raceway]]\n| [[Launceston, Tasmania|Launceston]], [[Tasmania]]\n| 8 - 9 Mar\n| Robbie Francevic\n| Mark Petch Motorsport\n| <ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8amnaocNIhg&ebc=ANyPxKpKOXDiQgq7yZoJZ_dhPXAcJMaZ1lmx0s1JEnWzdPT5sA8RHf3BnOa5Eedlh0ratRyMOxEQN6gVYQQYSPc1edcMaMWreA 1986 ATCC Symmons Plains Round 2]</ref>\n|-\n! 3\n| [[Castrol]] [[Sandown ATCC round|Challenge]]\n| [[Sandown International Raceway]]\n| [[Melbourne]], [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]]\n| 12 - 13 Apr\n| [[George Fury]]\n| [[Gibson Motorsport|Peter Jackson Nissan Racing]]\n| <ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4PwZPxhcFSc 1986 Sandown ATCC R3]</ref>\n|-\n! 4\n| [[Motorcraft]] [[Adelaide ATCC round|100]]\n| [[Adelaide International Raceway]]\n| [[Adelaide]], [[South Australia]]\n| 26 - 27 Apr\n| Robbie Francevic\n| [[Volvo Dealer Team]]\n| \n|-\n! 5\n| [[Motorcraft]] [[Wanneroo ATCC round|100]]\n| [[Wanneroo Park]]\n| [[Perth, Western Australia|Perth]], [[Western Australia]]\n| 5\u20136 May\n| George Fury\n| Peter Jackson Nissan Racing\n| <ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=22ckiXuyMjk 1986 ATCC Barbagello Round 5]</ref>\n|-\n! 6\n| [[Castlemaine XXXX|XXXX]] [[Surfers Paradise ATCC round|100]]\n| [[Surfers Paradise Raceway]]\n| [[Surfers Paradise]], [[Queensland]]\n| 17\u201318 May\n| [[Peter Brock]]\n| [[Mobil Holden Dealer Team]]\n| <ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xblpljI1blc 1986 ATCC Surfers Paradise R 6]</ref>\n|-\n! 7\n| [[Coca-Cola]] [[Calder Park ATCC round|Cup]]\n| [[Calder Park Raceway]]\n| [[Melbourne]], [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]]\n| 31 May - 1 Jun\n| George Fury\n| Peter Jackson Nissan Racing\n| <ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=L6GBIey5JKI 1986 ATCC Calder Park Round 7]</ref>\n|-\n! 8\n| [[Motorcraft]] [[Lakeside ATCC round|100]]\n| [[Lakeside International Raceway]]\n| [[Brisbane, Queensland|Brisbane]], [[Queensland]]\n| 14 - 15 Jun\n| George Fury\n| Peter Jackson Nissan Racing\n| <ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=knAVko8w1mk 1986 ATCC Lakeside Round 8]</ref>\n|-\n! 9\n| [[Winton ATCC round|Lusty-Allison Winton Roundup]]\n| [[Winton Motor Raceway]]\n| [[Benalla, Victoria|Benalla]], [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]]\n| 28 - 29 Jun\n| [[Jim Richards (race driver)|Jim Richards]]\n| [[JPS Team BMW]]\n| <ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VrNopnWg8Qs 1986 ATCC R9 Winton]</ref>\n|-\n! 10\n| [[Castrol]] [[Oran Park ATCC round|Grand Final]]\n| [[Oran Park Raceway]]\n| [[Sydney]], [[New South Wales]]\n| 12 - 13 Jul\n| George Fury\n| Peter Jackson Nissan Racing\n|\n|}\n\n===Drivers Championship===\nPoints were awarded 25-23-20-17-15-13-11-10-9-8-7-6-4-3-2-1 based on the top 17 outright race positions. The two smaller engine capacity classes received bonus points. Class B, under 3.0 litres received 3 points additional to points scored from race position. Class C, under 2.0 litres received 4 points.\n\nClass A consisted of [[BMW E24|BMW 635 CSi]], [[Third-generation Ford Mustang|Ford Mustang GT]], [[Ford Sierra XR4Ti]], [[Holden Commodore SS Group A|Holden VK Commodore SS Group A]], [[Jaguar XJS]], [[Rover SD1|Rover Vitesse]].\n\nClass B consisted of [[Alfa Romeo Alfetta|Alfa Romeo GTV6]], [[BMW E30|BMW 323i]], [[BMW E30|BMW 325i]], [[Mazda RX-7]], [[Mitsubishi Starion|Mitsubishi Starion Turbo]], [[Nissan Skyline|Nissan Skyline DR30 RS]], [[Toyota Supra]] and [[Volvo 200 Series|Volvo 240T]].\n\nClass C consisted of [[Isuzu Gemini|Holden Gemini]], [[Nissan Gazelle]], [[Toyota Celica]] and [[Toyota Corolla]].\n\n{|\n|\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 8